Inscription at the end of S1 part: "Informacia | Każda stropha kończy się szerokim przekrysleniem | gdzie znaczy piano. [underlined] tam trzeba Głos przyciszać; gdzie zaś iest | forte. [underlined] tam Echo głośno wydawać; wostatniey zaś strofie | po każdym słowie parce. [underlined] trzeba wszystkim przestać | razem wytrzymując iak puł [!] taktu y znowu razem zaczy | nać" [An information: Each stanza ends with a wide line. Where "piano" is written, the voice should be suppressed, while where "forte" is written, echo loud emitted. In the last stanza after each word "parce" all should stop and intermit for a half bar, and [then] start again].

Inscription at the end of A part: "Informacia [underlined] Wszystkie tu te strofy | co ywpierwszym głosie lubo po trzy | wiersze na iednę Linią pisane, dla że | ton ieden wychodzi oprocz ostatniey | przeto dobierać sobie łatwo potraficie | spiewa się zawsze iedna z tego kantu strofa | a druga zwyczaynym chorałem, tak iak iest | w Xięgach, yznowu ztey karty jedna, ytak na | przemiany i / że to się spiewa na 4 głosy, to | my tak dobieramy zpierszego głosu, dobiera | my wtorem a z altu dobieramy Basem | tylko gdzie napisano piano to [illegible] | to na ten czas przestaję Bas spiewać" [An information: All the stanzas here, which are written in the first part as three verses for a one line, because the melody is the same besides the last one, so you can easily fit. Always one from this cantional and the second as ordinary plainchant, as there is in books, is to be sung, and again from this card and again for a change. And as this is to be sung for 4 parts, thus we from the first part fit from the second and to Alt part fit from the Bas, only where "piano" is written, Bass stops to sing].

Apart from "REGESTR..." source contains a.o.: Gregorian chant, descriptions of monastic ceremonies, sacred songs, polyphonic masses, texts of songs and prayers for different liturgical feasts, meditation about liturgy of a mass, fragments of Roman Missal and Gradual, principles of music and singing (with exercises) and some empty pages in between.

Dedication on f. 1v of the cover: "Te Xiąszki są napisane Roku 1750 | od Maryanny Moszynskiey która za pozwoleniem | Przełożoney, daie nawiązanie sercem kochaney sie | strze swey Scholastyce Moszynskiey Z.R.OJ.B. | z zyczeniem nigdy nieokryslonym wszelkich łask Bło | gosławienst Boskich |:nie tylko ile tu literer [!] not & | y winnych tegoż mizernego Pisania Xioszkach ieyże da | nych:| ale co tylko się znayduie wyrażonych we wszystkich | Bibliotekach po całym świecie Xięgach" [These books were written in 1750 by Marianna Moszyńska, who, with her superior's permission, gives them to her beloved sister Scholastica, the Nun of the Rule of Saint Father Benedict, on her nameday[.] With the wish of never-ending all God's graces and blessings, as numerous as the letters and notes of this book and others of my poor writing given to her, but also in other books that are in libraries all over the world.]

Siemianowska X[ieni] | ZOSB mpr"[A.D. 1796, 13 April: I give forever to the choir this handwritten book with masses and other music, being the work of Jadwiga Dygulska's OSB own hands; she left it as her rememberance and it is our duty to remember about her soul. The abbess orders everyone that it be not neglected but highly esteemed as presumably no one will ever bring themselves to leave such a splendid souvenir apart from Ms Marianna Moszyńska and Jadwiga Dygulska who left the greatest books for playing and singing as souvenirs and to the glory of God. We shall always remember about their souls before God. M. Siemianowska]
The source contains pieces for Canto and figured bass, instrumental keyboard pieces and didactic remarks.
Three loose cards of different sizes, kinds of paper and copyist's hands with unidentified Mass fragments at the end of the book.

164 pages numbered by the copyist. Until the 51 page: plainchant or pseudoplainchant masses with figured bass for some Patrem movements (masses without records: Easter, Solemn, Apostolic, for Duplex Feasts, for regular Sundays, Saturday's votive, for Corpus Christi, Rorate, Requiem, for Christmas, "Msza Kasinska" [Casinensis], "Msza Farwanska" [Carter's mass?], pp. 1-18), Canto part and figured bass for masses and mass movements (pp. 19-50). Blank pages 46-47. Some didactic remarks on principles of music written on the pages 49-50. 139 solo compositions intended for a keyboard instrument written on pages 51-164 (with the exception of two missing cards with pages numbered 117-120).
Inscription at the top of p. 59: "L[aus] I[esu] H[risti] amen | Patybulum I: P: Dygulski y dobtodzieyce moi donożek u padam" [Patibulum I. P. Dygulska (?) and I fall at my benefactress feet]
